{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1071,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":2247,"text":"I present to you the human genome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4398,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":8301,"text":"Chromosome one -- top left,\nbottom right -- are the sex chromosomes."},{"time":12258,"text":"Women have two copies\nof that big X chromosome;"},{"time":15010,"text":"men have the X and, of course,\nthat small copy of the Y."},{"time":18199,"text":"Sorry boys, but it's just a tiny\nlittle thing that makes you different."},{"time":21914,"text":"So if you zoom in on this genome,"},{"time":24930,"text":"then what you see, of course,\nis this double-helix structure --"},{"time":28572,"text":"the code of life spelled out\nwith these four biochemical letters,"},{"time":31730,"text":"or we call them bases: A, C, G and T."},{"time":34000,"text":"How many are there\nin the human genome? Three billion."},{"time":36596,"text":"Is that a big number?"},{"time":37800,"text":"Well, everybody\ncan throw around big numbers."},{"time":40043,"text":"But in fact, if I were to place one base"},{"time":42167,"text":"on each pixel of this\n1280x800-resolution screen,"},{"time":45954,"text":"we would need 3,000 screens\nto take a look at the genome."},{"time":49257,"text":"So it's really quite big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50489,"text":"And perhaps because of its size,"},{"time":52408,"text":"a group of people -- all,\nby the way, with Y chromosomes --"},{"time":55283,"text":"decided they would want to sequence it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57317,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":59356,"text":"And so 15 years, actually,\nand about four billion dollars later,"},{"time":62637,"text":"the genome was sequenced and published."},{"time":64536,"text":"In 2003, the final version was published,\nand they keep working on it."},{"time":67880,"text":"That was all done on a machine like this."},{"time":69893,"text":"It costs about a dollar for each base --\na very slow way of doing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73234,"text":"Well, folks, I'm here to tell you"},{"time":74853,"text":"that the world has completely changed,"},{"time":76968,"text":"and none of you know about it."},{"time":78802,"text":"So now what we do is take a genome,"},{"time":81515,"text":"we make maybe 50 copies of it,"},{"time":83078,"text":"we cut all those copies up\ninto little 50-base reads,"},{"time":86122,"text":"and then we sequence them,\nmassively parallel."},{"time":88487,"text":"Then we bring that into software\nand reassemble it,"},{"time":91598,"text":"and tell you what the story is."},{"time":93192,"text":"So to give you a picture\nof what this looks like,"},{"time":95531,"text":"the Human Genome Project:\n3 gigabases, right?"},{"time":98038,"text":"One run on one of these modern machines:\n200 gigabases in a week."},{"time":102714,"text":"And that 200 is going\nto change to 600 this summer,"},{"time":105251,"text":"and there's no sign of this pace slowing."},{"time":107809,"text":"The price of a base, to sequence a base,"},{"time":111418,"text":"has fallen 100 million times."},{"time":114195,"text":"That's the equivalent of you filling up\nyour car with gas in 1998,"},{"time":117995,"text":"waiting until 2011,"},{"time":119248,"text":"and now you can drive\nto Jupiter and back twice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121685,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":126449,"text":"World population,"},{"time":128861,"text":"PC placements,"},{"time":130711,"text":"the archive of all of medical literature,"},{"time":133497,"text":"Moore's law,"},{"time":135219,"text":"the old way of sequencing,"},{"time":137072,"text":"and here's all the new stuff."},{"time":138853,"text":"Guys, this is a long scale;"},{"time":140218,"text":"you don't typically see\nlines that go up like that."},{"time":143442,"text":"So the worldwide capacity\nto sequence human genomes"},{"time":146924,"text":"is something like 50,000 to 100,000\nhuman genomes this year."},{"time":150117,"text":"We know this based on the machines\nthat are being placed."},{"time":152844,"text":"This is expected to double,\ntriple or maybe quadruple"},{"time":155385,"text":"year over year for the foreseeable future."},{"time":157619,"text":"In fact, there's one lab in particular"},{"time":159628,"text":"that represents 20 percent\nof all that capacity:"},{"time":162588,"text":"It's called the Beijing\nGenomics Institute."},{"time":165406,"text":"The Chinese are absolutely winning\nthis race to the new Moon, by the way."},{"time":169135,"text":"What does this mean for medicine?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":171460,"text":"So a woman, age 37,"},{"time":174208,"text":"presents with stage 2 estrogen\nreceptor-positive breast cancer."},{"time":177446,"text":"She is treated with surgery,\nchemotherapy and radiation."},{"time":180637,"text":"She goes home."},{"time":181845,"text":"Two years later,"},{"time":183020,"text":"she comes back with stage 3C\novarian cancer, unfortunately;"},{"time":186218,"text":"treated again with surgery\nand chemotherapy."},{"time":188679,"text":"She comes back three years later at age 42"},{"time":190957,"text":"with more ovarian cancer,\nmore chemotherapy."},{"time":193338,"text":"Six months later,"},{"time":194831,"text":"she comes back\nwith acute myeloid leukemia."},{"time":199559,"text":"She goes into respiratory failure\nand dies eight days later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202589,"text":"So first: the way in which\nthis woman was treated,"},{"time":204971,"text":"in as little as 10 years,\nwill look like bloodletting."},{"time":208438,"text":"And it's because of people\nlike my colleague, Rick Wilson,"},{"time":211287,"text":"at the Genome Institute\nat Washington University,"},{"time":213650,"text":"who decided to take a look\nat this woman postmortem."},{"time":216133,"text":"And he took skin cells, healthy skin"},{"time":218640,"text":"and cancerous bone marrow,"},{"time":220602,"text":"and sequenced the whole\ngenomes of both of them"},{"time":222912,"text":"in a couple of weeks, no big deal."},{"time":225000,"text":"Then he compared those two\ngenomes in software,"},{"time":227225,"text":"and what he found, among other things,"},{"time":229074,"text":"was a deletion -- a 2,000-base deletion\nacross three billion bases"},{"time":233711,"text":"in a particular gene called TP53."},{"time":235894,"text":"If you have this deleterious\nmutation in this gene,"},{"time":238330,"text":"you're 90 percent likely\nto get cancer in your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241076,"text":"So unfortunately,\nthis doesn't help this woman,"},{"time":243324,"text":"but it does have severe --\nprofound, if you will --"},{"time":246000,"text":"implications to her family."},{"time":248801,"text":"I mean, if they have the same mutation,"},{"time":250708,"text":"and they get this genetic test\nand they understand it,"},{"time":253277,"text":"then they can get regular screens\nand can catch cancer early,"},{"time":256182,"text":"and potentially live\na significantly longer life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258526,"text":"Let me introduce you to the Beery twins,"},{"time":260480,"text":"diagnosed with cerebral palsy\nat the age of two."},{"time":262836,"text":"Their mom is a very brave woman\nwho didn't believe it;"},{"time":265408,"text":"the symptoms weren't matching up."},{"time":267035,"text":"And through some heroic efforts\nand a lot of Internet searching,"},{"time":270067,"text":"she was able to convince\nthe medical community"},{"time":272262,"text":"that, in fact, they had something else."},{"time":274182,"text":"They had dopa-responsive dystonia."},{"time":276372,"text":"And so they were given L-Dopa,"},{"time":278375,"text":"and their symptoms did improve,"},{"time":280716,"text":"but they weren't totally asymptomatic."},{"time":282583,"text":"Significant problems remained."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284074,"text":"Turns out the gentleman in this picture\nis a guy named Joe Beery,"},{"time":287267,"text":"who was lucky enough to be the CIO"},{"time":288934,"text":"of a company called Life Technologies."},{"time":291079,"text":"They're one of two companies"},{"time":292445,"text":"that makes these massive\nwhole-genome sequencing tools."},{"time":295619,"text":"And so he got his kids sequenced."},{"time":298656,"text":"What they found was a series of mutations\nin a gene called SPR,"},{"time":301758,"text":"which is responsible for producing\nserotonin, among other things."},{"time":305179,"text":"So on top of L-Dopa, they gave\nthese kids a serotonin precursor drug,"},{"time":308692,"text":"and they're effectively normal now."},{"time":310438,"text":"Guys, this would never have happened\nwithout whole-genome sequencing."},{"time":313753,"text":"At the time -- this was\na few years ago -- it cost $100,000."},{"time":316617,"text":"Today it's $10,000, next year, $1,000,"},{"time":318468,"text":"the year after, $100, give or take a year."},{"time":320521,"text":"That's how fast this is moving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322045,"text":"So here's little Nick --"},{"time":323926,"text":"likes Batman and squirt guns."},{"time":325666,"text":"And it turns out Nick\nshows up at the children's hospital"},{"time":329385,"text":"with this distended belly,\nlike a famine victim."},{"time":331671,"text":"And it's not that he's not eating;\nit's that when he eats,"},{"time":334531,"text":"his intestine basically opens up\nand feces spill out into his gut."},{"time":337966,"text":"So a hundred surgeries later,"},{"time":339625,"text":"he looks at his mom and says,\n\"Mom, please pray for me."},{"time":343324,"text":"I'm in so much pain.\""},{"time":345148,"text":"His pediatrician happens to have\na background in clinical genetics"},{"time":348287,"text":"and he has no idea what's going on,"},{"time":350000,"text":"but he says, \"Let's get\nthis kid's genome sequenced.\""},{"time":352567,"text":"And what they find\nis a single-point mutation"},{"time":354731,"text":"in a gene responsible for controlling\nprogrammed cell death."},{"time":357604,"text":"So the theory is that he's having\nsome immunological reaction"},{"time":360706,"text":"to what's going on --\nto the food, essentially."},{"time":363145,"text":"And that's a natural reaction,\nwhich causes some programmed cell death,"},{"time":366539,"text":"but the gene that regulates\nthat down is broken."},{"time":368833,"text":"And so this informs,\namong other things, of course,"},{"time":371275,"text":"a treatment for bone marrow transplant,\nwhich he undertakes."},{"time":374270,"text":"And after nine months\nof grueling recovery,"},{"time":376314,"text":"he's now eating steak with A1 sauce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378243,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379364,"text":"The prospect of using the genome\nas a universal diagnostic"},{"time":383487,"text":"is upon us today."},{"time":386202,"text":"Today. It's here."},{"time":387765,"text":"And what it means for all of us"},{"time":389281,"text":"is that everybody in this room\ncould live an extra 5, 10, 20 years,"},{"time":392592,"text":"just because of this one thing."},{"time":394283,"text":"Which is a fantastic story,"},{"time":396370,"text":"unless you think about\nhumanity's footprint on the planet,"},{"time":399272,"text":"and our ability to keep up\nfood production."},{"time":401771,"text":"So it turns out"},{"time":403367,"text":"that the very same technology\nis also being used to grow new lines"},{"time":407332,"text":"of corn, wheat, soybean and other crops"},{"time":410485,"text":"that are highly tolerant\nof drought, of flood,"},{"time":412684,"text":"of pests and pesticides."},{"time":414231,"text":"Now, look --"},{"time":415924,"text":"as long as we continue\nto increase the population,"},{"time":418322,"text":"we'll have to continue to grow and eat\ngenetically modified foods."},{"time":421525,"text":"And that's the only position\nI'll take today."},{"time":423700,"text":"Unless there's anybody in the audience"},{"time":425542,"text":"who'd like to volunteer to stop eating?"},{"time":427787,"text":"None, not one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429701,"text":"This is a typewriter,"},{"time":431436,"text":"a staple of every desktop for decades."},{"time":434079,"text":"And, in fact, the typewriter\nwas essentially deleted by this thing."},{"time":438243,"text":"And then more general versions\nof word processors came about."},{"time":441532,"text":"But ultimately, it was a disruption\non top of a disruption."},{"time":444335,"text":"It was Bob Metcalfe\ninventing the Ethernet,"},{"time":446427,"text":"and the connection of all these computers"},{"time":448420,"text":"that fundamentally changed everything."},{"time":450294,"text":"Suddenly we had Netscape, we had Yahoo."},{"time":453119,"text":"And we had, indeed,\nthe entire dot-com bubble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456688,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459520,"text":"Not to worry though,"},{"time":460767,"text":"that was quickly rescued\nby the iPod, Facebook"},{"time":463366,"text":"and, indeed, Angry Birds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465493,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467865,"text":"Look, this is where we are today."},{"time":470415,"text":"This is the genomic revolution today.\nThis is where we are."},{"time":473229,"text":"What I'd like you to consider is:"},{"time":474833,"text":"What does it mean"},{"time":476262,"text":"when these dots don't represent\nthe individual bases of your genome,"},{"time":479643,"text":"but they connect to genomes\nall across the planet?"},{"time":482518,"text":"I just recently had to buy life insurance,\nand I was required to answer:"},{"time":486130,"text":"A. I have never had a genetic test;"},{"time":488285,"text":"B. I've had one, here you go;"},{"time":489792,"text":"or C. I've had one and I'm not telling."},{"time":491761,"text":"Thankfully, I was able to answer A,"},{"time":493501,"text":"and I say that honestly, in case\nmy life insurance agent is listening."},{"time":497073,"text":"But what would have happened\nif I had said C?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":499496,"text":"Consumer applications\nfor genomics will flourish."},{"time":501921,"text":"Do you want to see\nif you're genetically compatible"},{"time":504394,"text":"with your girlfriend?"},{"time":505648,"text":"DNA sequencing on your iPhone?\nThere's an app for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508635,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510445,"text":"Personalized genomic massage, anyone?"},{"time":513778,"text":"There's already a lab today that tests\nfor allele 334 of the AVPR1 gene,"},{"time":518369,"text":"the so-called cheating gene."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519777,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521816,"text":"So anybody who's here today\nwith your significant other,"},{"time":524467,"text":"just turn over to them,\nswab their mouth, send it to the lab"},{"time":527358,"text":"and you'll know for sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528651,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":529786,"text":"Do you really want to elect a president"},{"time":531752,"text":"whose genome suggests cardiomyopathy?"},{"time":534038,"text":"Think of it -- it's 2016,"},{"time":535922,"text":"and the leading candidate releases"},{"time":537652,"text":"not only her four years\nof back-tax returns,"},{"time":539758,"text":"but also her personal genome."},{"time":541235,"text":"And it looks really good."},{"time":542469,"text":"Then she challenges all\nher competitors to do the same."},{"time":545089,"text":"Do you think that's not going to happen?"},{"time":547048,"text":"Do you think it would have\nhelped John McCain?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":549306,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":551123,"text":"How many people in the audience\nhave the last name Resnick, like me?"},{"time":554365,"text":"Raise your hand."},{"time":555547,"text":"Anybody? Nobody."},{"time":557175,"text":"Typically, there's one or two."},{"time":558644,"text":"So my father's father\nwas one of 10 Resnick brothers."},{"time":561221,"text":"They all hated each other, and all moved\nto different parts of the planet."},{"time":565330,"text":"So it's likely I'm related\nto every Resnick that I ever meet,"},{"time":568273,"text":"but I don't know."},{"time":569448,"text":"So imagine if my genome\nwere De-identified, sitting in software,"},{"time":572509,"text":"And a third cousin's genome\nwas also sitting there,"},{"time":574917,"text":"and there was software\nthat could compare the two"},{"time":577242,"text":"and make these associations."},{"time":578623,"text":"Not hard to imagine. My company\nhas software that does this right now."},{"time":581955,"text":"Imagine one more thing,"},{"time":583147,"text":"that that software is able to ask\nboth parties for mutual consent:"},{"time":586406,"text":"\"Would you be willing\nto meet your third cousin?\""},{"time":588755,"text":"And if we both say yes -- voilà!"},{"time":590429,"text":"Welcome to Chromosomally LinkedIn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592230,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":596548,"text":"Now this is probably a good thing, right?"},{"time":598565,"text":"Bigger clan gatherings and so on."},{"time":600177,"text":"But maybe it's a bad thing as well."},{"time":601902,"text":"How many fathers in the room?\nRaise your hands."},{"time":604207,"text":"OK, so experts think\nthat one to three percent of you"},{"time":607559,"text":"are not actually the father of your child."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609686,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":611464,"text":"Look --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":612664,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":617611,"text":"These genomes, these 23 chromosomes,"},{"time":620000,"text":"they don't in any way represent\nthe quality of our relationships"},{"time":623389,"text":"or the nature of our society --\nat least not yet."},{"time":626106,"text":"And like any new technology,"},{"time":627925,"text":"it's really in humanity's hands"},{"time":629738,"text":"to wield it for the betterment of mankind"},{"time":631960,"text":"or not."},{"time":633135,"text":"And so I urge you all\nto wake up and to tune in"},{"time":635382,"text":"and to influence the genomic revolution\nthat's happening all around you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638802,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639977,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}